    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How much weight do women gain on creatine?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Most women gain 1-3 pounds within the first 2-4 weeks of creatine supplementation. This weight is intracellular water inside muscle tissue, not body fat. The water gain stabilizes after the saturation phase. Over months of consistent training, additional weight gain may come from actual lean muscle mass increases (typically 1-3 pounds over 12 weeks), but this represents desirable lean mass rather than body fat. Total body fat does not increase from creatine.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Does creatine make a visible difference in women?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes, but the visible difference is more subtle than the strength and recovery benefits. Most noticeable visible changes are: increased muscle fullness (especially in shoulders, arms, and quads), improved muscle definition over 8-12 weeks combined with resistance training, and in some women slight reduction in subcutaneous fat as lean mass increases support resting metabolic rate. Dramatic photo-worthy transformations require months of training combined with appropriate nutrition — creatine accelerates these changes but does not produce them alone.' },
    },
