      <details class="fq"><summary>How long does it take to see creatine results in women?</summary><p>Most women notice changes within 2-4 weeks of consistent daily supplementation. Earliest effect is muscle fullness from intracellular water (1-3 lb scale gain). Strength improvements emerge in weeks 3-6. Visible body composition changes typically take 8-12 weeks with resistance training. Cognitive benefits appear within 4-8 weeks.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What does creatine before and after look like for women?</summary><p>Most common changes: more visible muscle tone in arms, shoulders, and quads; fuller, less flat appearance to muscles; modest 1-3 pound weight gain (intracellular water); reductions in body fat percentage as lean mass increases. Changes are subtle in the first month and accelerate through months 2-4.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Will I see changes from creatine without working out?</summary><p>Yes, but limited. Without resistance training, you still get the 1-3 lb water gain (fuller muscles), cognitive support, and lean mass preservation during aging. But dramatic strength, power, and visible body composition changes require creatine plus training. Without training, you get maybe 20% of creatine's potential.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>How much weight do women gain on creatine?</summary><p>1-3 pounds in the first 2-4 weeks (intracellular water in muscle tissue, not body fat). Weight stabilizes after saturation. Over months of training, additional 1-3 pounds may come from actual lean muscle mass. Total body fat does not increase from creatine.</p></details>
