      <details class="fq"><summary>Should women take creatine pictures to track progress?</summary><p>Yes — weekly progress photos are far more useful than scale weight. Take front, side, back photos in consistent lighting, posture, and clothing every 1-2 weeks. Most women see meaningful visible changes by week 6-8, dramatic by month 3-4 with consistent training.</p></details>
